On Sunday, we lost an hour of sleep as clocks sprung forward from 2 a.m. to 3 a.m. to mark the annual shift to daylight saving time. Sunsets now happen later in the day, but that comes at the price of a precious hour of sleep. If you are feeling groggy and grumpy today, you are not alone. A lot of us are still catching up on rest after this annual spring ritual and want to complain. Here are some of the funniest tweets about springing forward and daylight saving time: